description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;33.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit a highly motivated, approachable and committed individual to join Redcar and Cleveland Council’s Occupational Therapy (OT) team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Occupational Therapy team are dedicated to supporting people to remain independent in their own home. The team work with people in the Borough who have difficulties managing everyday activities of daily living because of age or disability. We assess for the provision of equipment and adaptations. The progress coordinator is a key member of the team in ensuring that the service is delivered in an effective and efficient way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have good verbal communication skills, (including over the telephone) but also be able to quickly produce accurate typed records as we use an electronic client record system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is part of the Integrated Occupational Therapy service across South Tees giving wide access to peer support, staff development and integrated working practices across health and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this vacancy will close when we receive sufficient completed applications.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pat Coates (Therapy Manager)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: Patricia.Coates@redcar-cleveland.gov.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 07584 703069&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
